    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 1 },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Three state DOTs share one corridor — with no central authority.\n\nMARDOT, VELDOT, and SABDOT each run their own network of ~33 cabinets — 99 in all — with their own NATS JetStream tiers and their own ClickHouse database. Vikasa federates their I-85 corridor data in real time through a one-way DMZ boundary — every cabinet event stays sovereign at the edge and visible at the center. No shared control plane. No single point of failure. Just open standards and JetStream leaf-node replication."
      },
      "title": "",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 6 },
